§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A ❬base❭ $ℬ$ for a topology $𝒯$ on a set $X$ is a subset
    of $𝒯$ such that every open set $U ∈ 𝒯$ is a union of a
    family of sets in $ℬ$. ⦉
